OL,5,G0445 James Martin's American Adventure
OL,6,     FThe chef begins the Texan leg of
OL,7,     Fhis journey in San Antonio, a city
OL,8,     Fwhich was once part of Mexico.
OL,9,     FHere, James samples traditional
OL,10,     Ftamales and barbecoa at the hands
OL,11,     Fof the city's most famous chef,
OL,12,     FJohnny Hernandez. The chef also
OL,13,     Ftries authentic street food in the
OL,14,     Fform of hot, fresh chorros, and
OL,15,     Flearns about the famous San
OL,16,     FAntonio Chilli Queens
